# Go Coding Style

- Prefer package-level interface + private `impl` when test seams are needed.
- Keep constructor shape: `New(...) <InterfaceOrConcrete>` with explicit deps.
- Keep functions small; use named return (`func X() (result T, err error)`) with `defer` only when it clarifies lifecycle/error handling.
- Naming style:
  - Exported: `PascalCase`; unexported: `camelCase`.
  - Constructors: `NewX(...)`.
  - Interfaces: behavior-first names (`Usecase`, `RouteRegistrar`, `TxManager`), avoid generic `I*`.
  - Keep names short but specific (`runtimeRepo`, `validatorRegistrars`, `respondAppError`).
  - Avoid unclear abbreviations unless common in Go (`ctx`, `cfg`, `tx`, `id`).
- Keep comments short and intent-focused; avoid obvious comments.
